<br>
(Some pseduo mathematics for those so inclined.  If I roll 1-350 and everyone else rolls 1-300 I have better than a 1/7 chance to win (as 1/7 times I roll 301-350).  As you have more and more people rolling 1-350 the chances of a winning roll less than 300 becomes close to zero.  On the other hand if I roll 51-300 my chances of rolling in the last group of 50 is now 1/5 instead of 1/6.  My odds of winning are improved by that same margin.  But the odds are much less in my favor and everyone has a reasonable chance to win.)<br>
<br>
-Dword<br>
